<TITLE> Sampdoria name Del Neri as coach </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MILAN, June 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sampdoria have named Gigi Del Neri as their new coach after the departure of Walter Mazzarri, the Serie A club said in a statement on Monday. Former AS Roma and Chievo boss Del Neri had already announced he would be leaving Atalanta after two solid years and has been appointed just a day after the end of the campaign. Atalanta and Sampdoria both finished in mid-table with Samp losing the Italian Cup final to Lazio, prompting the club not to renew Mazzarri's contract
